      border-top: 1px solid #DDD9D5;
      padding-top: 40px;
    }
</style>

<div class="ab-lazy-function" data-lazy-function="lazyAdsenseContent" id="adsenseContainer"></div>

<script charset="utf-8"> 

   window.lazyFunctions = window.lazyFunctions || {};
   window.lazyFunctions.lazyAdsenseContent = function (element) {
      const qVal = AB.COMMON.getURLParameterByName('q');
      const disallowedSearchTerms = ["flower", "flowers", "flower arrangement", "flower arrangements", "flower bouquet", "flower bouquets", "flower delivery", "flowers delivery", "flower deliveries", "fresh flower", "fresh flowers", "rose", "roses"]; 
      
      if(qVal && disallowedSearchTerms.includes(qVal.toLowerCase()) == false){
         loadAdsenseContentLazy(qVal);
      }
   };
 
function loadAdsenseContentLazy (searchVal) {  

    $('<h2 class= "adSense-header">Sponsored products you may also like</h2>').
           insertBefore("#adsenseContainer");
   
    const pageOptions = {
      pubId: "partner-pub-8281163827971822",
      query: searchVal,
      styleId: "9728593315",
      adsafe: "high",
      number: "2",
      personalizedAds: false,
      linkTarget: "_blank"
    };
    const adblock1 = {
      container: "adsenseContainer",
    };
    _googCsa("ads", pageOptions, adblock1);

}

</script>

                        var targetStorage = localStorage.getItem(analyticsSwy.CONSTS.TARGET_STORAGE);
                        targetStorage = targetStorage ? JSON.parse(targetStorage) : {};
                        targetStorage[key] = value;
                        localStorage.setItem(analyticsSwy.CONSTS.TARGET_STORAGE, JSON.stringify(targetStorage));
                    }
                },
                getLocalStorageItem: function (path) {
                    try {
                        if (window.localStorage && path !== undefined) {
                            var targetStorageObject = localStorage.getItem(analyticsSwy.CONSTS.TARGET_STORAGE);
                            if (targetStorageObject) {
                                targetStorageObject = JSON.parse(targetStorageObject);
                                if (path && typeof path === 'string') {

                        return null;
                    } catch (e) {
                        analyticsSwy.utils.setTargetError("getLocalStorageItem failed:" + e);
                    }

                safelyReadProperty: function (pathToProperty, start) {

                    pathToProperty = (pathToProperty || []);
                    pathToProperty = (
                        (typeof pathToProperty === "string") ? pathToProperty.split(".") : pathToProperty
                    );
                    for (i = 0; i < pathToProperty.length; i += 1) {
                        if (currentLocation[pathToProperty[i]] != undefined) {
                            currentLocation = currentLocation[pathToProperty[i]];
                            if (i === pathToProperty.length - 1) {
                                return (currentLocation);
                            }
                        } else {
                            return "";
                        }
                    }
                },
                setTargetError: function (err) {
                    err = err || "Error not defined";
                    if (tFuncs.pathName && tFuncs.storeIdJ4U && tFuncs.storeIdSHOP) {

                    } else {

                    }
                    window.console.warn('[Target Error]:' + err);
                },
                setTargetErrorRequest: function (err) {

                    analyticsSwy.errors += (err + ';');

                    if (nameEvent !== undefined && valueEvent !== undefined) {
                        window.dispatchEvent(new CustomEvent(nameEvent, {
                            "detail": valueEvent
                        }));
                    }
                },
                setTargetFlag: function (key, value) {
                    if (key !== undefined && value !== undefined) {
                        window.analyticsSwy.testFlags[key] = value;
                        this.triggerCustomEvent(key, {
                            [key]: value
                        });
                    }
                },
                parseStringToJSON: function (obj) {
                    if (obj !== undefined) {
                        try {
                            obj = JSON.parse(obj);
                            if (obj && typeof obj === "object") {
                                return obj;
                            }
                        } catch (error) {
                            window.analyticsSwy.utils.setTargetError('parseStringToJSON: "' + obj + '": ' + error);
                        }
                    }
                    return {};
                }
            }
        },
        implementTTMeta: /* istanbul ignore next */ function (e) {
            /************ ttMETA Implementation for at.js > 2.x *************/
            function isEmpty(val) {
                return (
                    Boolean(val === undefined || val === null || val.length <= 0)
                );
            }

            function key(obj) {
                return Object.keys(obj)
                    .map(function (k) {
                        return String(k) + String(obj[k]);
                    })
                    .join("");
            }

            function distinct(arr) {
                var result = arr.reduce(function (acc, e) {
                    acc[key(e)] = e;
                    return acc;
                }, {});
                return Object.keys(result)
                    .map(function (k) {
                        return result[k];
                    });
            }
            window.ttMETA = (
                window.ttMETA !== undefined ? window.ttMETA : []
            );
            /* We are intermittently seeing duplicate info in ttMETA after signing in on QA2.
             ** This is happening because 'at-request-succeeded' was being fired twice for some reason.
             ** That is why I am running the following code which will just stop this function if ttMETA
             ** is already populated */
            if (window.ttMETA.length === 0) {
                var tokens = e.detail.responseTokens;
                if (isEmpty(tokens)) {
                    return;
                }
                var uniqueTokens = distinct(tokens);
                /* Added by Mike to remove any tokens which had the same activity
                 ** TO-DO: We need to make Adobe aware of this issue so they can fix from their end */
                uniqueTokens.forEach(function (currTok, indx, origin) {
                    var name = currTok['activity.name'];
                    var i;
                    if (name) {
                        for (i = (indx + 1); i < origin.length; i += 1) {
                            if (name === origin[i]['activity.name']) {
                                uniqueTokens.splice(i, 1);
                                i = i - 1;
                            }
                        }
                    }
                });
                uniqueTokens.forEach(function (token) {
                    window.ttMETA.push({
                        'CampaignName': token["activity.name"],
                        'CampaignId': token["activity.id"],
                        'RecipeName': token["experience.name"],
                        'RecipeId': token["experience.id"],
                        'OfferId': token["option.id"],
                        'OfferName': token["option.name"],
                        'MboxName': e.detail.mbox
                    });
                });
            }
            /************ End ttMETA Implementation *************/
        },
        setDebugger: /* istanbul ignore next */ function () {
            if (window.analyticsSwy.isDebugMode) {
                debugger;
            }
        }
    };
    //Make this object global
    window.analyticsSwy = tFuncs.analyticsSwy;
    tFuncs.setDebugger();
    /* Read these cookies once and store them as JSON once */
    analyticsSwy.storedData.SWY_SHARED_SESSION_INFO = analyticsSwy.utils.parseStringToJSON(_satellite.cookie.get(window.analyticsSwy.CONSTS.SWY_SHARED_SESSION_INFO));
    analyticsSwy.storedData.SWY_SHARED_PII_SESSION_INFO = analyticsSwy.utils.parseStringToJSON(_satellite.cookie.get(window.analyticsSwy.CONSTS.SWY_SHARED_PII_SESSION_INFO));
    tFuncs.storeIdSHOP = analyticsSwy.utils.safelyReadProperty('info.SHOP.storeId' , analyticsSwy.storedData.SWY_SHARED_SESSION_INFO );
    tFuncs.storeIdJ4U = analyticsSwy.utils.safelyReadProperty('info.J4U.storeId' , analyticsSwy.storedData.SWY_SHARED_SESSION_INFO );

    /**
     * Dispatches a custom event "at-identifiers" when all required Target identifiers are ready:
     * 1) ECID, 2) tntId, 3) sessionId, 4) SDID and optional 5) GUID with auth state (0, 1 or 2)
     * Code is listening to the following at.js events:
     * at-library-loaded, at-request-start, at-request-succeeded, at-request-failed
     * When the very first responding event contains all 4 valid identifiers, this event is triggered and passes those IDs
     * @version 0.0.3
     * @author Adobe Consulting, Vadym.Ustymenko@adobe.com
     * @usage
     * document.addEventListener("at-identifiers", function(e) {
     * console.log("Custom Event at-identifiers",e.detail.tntId, e.detail.sessionId, e.detail.marketingCloudVisitorId, e.detail.supplementalDataId)}, false);
     * (optional) console.log("Optional GUID", e.detail["vst.guid.id"], e.detail["vst.guid.authState"])
     *  }, false);
     **/

    var atFuncs = {
        VERSION: "0.0.3",
        didDispatchATIdentifiers: false,
        atIds: {},
        atEvents: [
            "at-library-loaded",
            "at-request-start",
            "at-request-succeeded",
            "at-request-failed",
            "at-content-rendering-failed",
            "at-content-rendering-succeeded",
            "at-content-rendering-no-offers"
        ],
        atCompleteEvents: [
            "at-request-failed",
            "at-content-rendering-failed",
            "at-content-rendering-succeeded",
            "at-content-rendering-no-offers"
        ],
        log: function () {
            if (window.analyticsSwy.isDebugMode) {
                Array.prototype.unshift.call(arguments, "AT-IDS:");
                console.warn.apply(window, arguments);
            }
        },
        dispatchATIdentifiersEvent: function (atIdentifiers) {
            var evt = new CustomEvent("at-identifiers", {
                "detail": atIdentifiers
            });
            document.dispatchEvent(evt);
            this.didDispatchATIdentifiers = true;
            this.log("Dispatched at-identifiers", atIdentifiers);
        },
        isIdenifierValid: function (idName) {
            return typeof idName === "string" && idName.length > 0;
        },
        prepareVisitorIdentifiers: function (atIdentifiers) {
            var visitor = window.Visitor.getInstance(window._satellite.getVar("AdobeOrg"));
            visitor.getVisitorValues(function (vals) {
                var ecid = vals["MCMID"];
                var sdid = visitor.getSupplementalDataID("recs-" + Math.random());
                if (atFuncs.isIdenifierValid(ecid) && atFuncs.isIdenifierValid(sdid)) {
                    atIdentifiers["marketingCloudVisitorId"] = ecid;
                    atIdentifiers["supplementalDataId"] = sdid;
                    var customerIds = visitor.getCustomerIDs();
                    if ("guid" in customerIds) {
                        var guid = customerIds["guid"];
                        atIdentifiers["vst.guid.id"] = guid.id;
                        atIdentifiers["vst.guid.authState"] = guid.authState;
                    }
                    atFuncs.atIds = atIdentifiers;
                    atFuncs.dispatchATIdentifiersEvent(atIdentifiers);
                    atFuncs.setStoreIds();
                }
            }, [visitor.FIELDS.MCMID]);
        },
        prepareATIdentifiers: function (tracking) {
            if (this.didDispatchATIdentifiers == false && typeof tracking === "object" && atFuncs.isIdenifierValid(tracking.deviceId) && atFuncs.isIdenifierValid(tracking.sessionId)) {
                this.prepareVisitorIdentifiers({
                    "tntId": tracking.deviceId,
                    "sessionId": tracking.sessionId
                });
            }
        },
        setStoreIds: function () {
            var storedIds = analyticsSwy.storedData.ids;
            //Store these Ids for the UI Code in case they missed the event.    
            storedIds.marketingCloudVisitorId = atFuncs.atIds["marketingCloudVisitorId"];
            storedIds.mboxMCSDID = atFuncs.atIds["supplementalDataId"];
            storedIds.sessionId = atFuncs.atIds.sessionId;
            storedIds.tntId = atFuncs.atIds.tntId;
            storedIds.edgeHost = "mboxedge" + storedIds.tntId.substring(
                storedIds.tntId.lastIndexOf(".") + 1,
                storedIds.tntId.lastIndexOf("_")
            ) + ".tt.omtrdc.net";
            //Store paramsForRecs for UI Code to use with Recs Carousels    
            storedIds.paramsForRecs = JSON.stringify(analyticsSwy.storedData.ids).replace((/"|{|}/g), '').replace(/:/g, '=').replace(/,/g, '&');
            //Store at_property Id for UI Code to use with Recs Carousels    
            storedIds.at_property = _satellite.getVar('target : at_property');
        },
        init: function () {
            for (var i = this.atEvents.length - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
                var atEvent = this.atEvents[i];
                document.addEventListener(atEvent, function (e) {
                    atFuncs.log(atEvent, e.detail);
                    atFuncs.prepareATIdentifiers(e.detail.tracking);
                    if (
                        e.detail.type == "at-request-succeeded" ||
                        e.detail.type == "at-request-failed"
                    ) {
                        tFuncs.implementTTMeta(e);
                        if (!atFuncs.didDispatchATIdentifiers) {
                            atFuncs.log("Target Identifiers did not have all required ids.");
                        }
                    }
                    //For tracking Target failures in analytics
                    if (e.detail.type == "at-request-failed") {
                        if (tFuncs.analyticsSwy.errors.indexOf("at-request-failed") === -1) {
                            tFuncs.analyticsSwy.utils.setTargetErrorRequest("at-request-failed" + " : " + tFuncs.analyticsSwy.utils.safelyReadProperty("detail.error.message", e));
                        }
                    }
                    //For other teams to know to stop waiting for our success flag / event
                    if (atFuncs.atCompleteEvents.indexOf(e.detail.type) != -1) {
                        tFuncs.analyticsSwy.utils.setTargetFlag("AdobeTarget-Complete", true);
                        tFuncs.analyticsSwy.utils.setTargetFlag("targetIsComplete", true);
                    }
                }, false);
            }
        }
    }
    try {
        atFuncs.init();
    } catch (e) {
        tFuncs.analyticsSwy.utils.setTargetError("Target Dependency JS file: " + e);
    }
}

(function () {
    function init() {
        var tvp = "AB_AT_";
 
        function sendToCS(csKey, csValue) {
            csKey = tvp + csKey;
 
            _uxa.push([
                "trackDynamicVariable",
                {
                    key: csKey,
                    value: csValue,
                },
            ]);
        }
 if (window.location.href.indexOf("sandeep") != -1){debugger;}
        function startATintegration() {
            setTimeout(function () {
                for (var i = 0; i < ttMETA.length; i++) {
                    var campaignName = "";
                    var variationName = "";
 
                    if (ttMETA[i]["CampaignName"] && ttMETA[i]["RecipeName"]) {
                        campaignName = ttMETA[i]["CampaignName"];
                        variationName = ttMETA[i]["RecipeName"];
                    } else if (ttMETA[i]["campaign"] && ttMETA[i]["experience"]) {
                        campaignName = ttMETA[i]["campaign"];
                        variationName = ttMETA[i]["experience"];
                    }
 
                    if (campaignName && variationName) {
                        sendToCS(campaignName, variationName);
                    }
                }
            }, 500);
        }
        var integrationStarted = false;
 
        var ttMETA = window.ttMETA;
        if (ttMETA) {
            startATintegration();
        } else {
            Object.defineProperty(window, "ttMETA", {
                configurable: true,
                get: function () {
                    return ttMETA;
                },
                set: function (n) {
                    ttMETA = n;
                    if (!integrationStarted) {
                        integrationStarted = true;
                        startATintegration();
                    }
                },
            });
        }
    }
 
    function callback() {
        if (!disableCallback) {
            disableCallback = true;
            init();
 
            if (window.CS_CONF) {
                CS_CONF.integrations = CS_CONF.integrations || [];
                CS_CONF.integrations.push("Adobe Target");
            }
        }
    }
 
    var disableCallback = false;
 
    window._uxa = window._uxa || [];
    _uxa.push(["afterPageView", callback]);
})();
//Adobe Target CS Integration End
